          <title>Florida bill would require some elementary school students to learn cursive</title>
          <description><![CDATA[TAMPA, Fla. (WFLA) — A new Florida bill would require some elementary school students to learn cursive writing. The bill, HB 921, would require all public schools to provide cursive writing instruction to students in grades 2 through 5.]]></description>
